text: The Cochiquito Volcanic Group is a small volcanic group of volcanoes north of the town of Buta Ranquil in Argentina. The main peak is Volcán Cochiquito, a stratovolcano of estimated Pleistocene–Holocene age. There are eight satellite cones in the volcanic field, including Volcán Sillanegra (a pyroclastic cone complex) and Volcán Ranquil del Sur (a small stratovolcano). ==See also== *List of volcanoes in Argentina ==Sources== * Category:Stratovolcanoes of Argentina Category:Andean Volcanic Belt Category:Volcanic groups Category:Subduction volcanoes Category:Mountains of Argentina
